WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:06.900 --> 00:00:10.480
A world... Yes!

3
00:00:10.480 --> 00:00:16.530
A world for you who seek freedom stretches out right before your eyes.

4
00:00:16.530 --> 00:00:20.410
If you feel guided by endless dreams,

5
00:00:20.410 --> 00:00:25.170
surpass them, flying the flag of your beliefs!

6
00:00:29.800 --> 00:00:35.480
I've just now begun to search, over the splashing waves

7
00:00:35.480 --> 00:00:38.630
For the everlasting world

8
00:00:39.930 --> 00:00:42.990
With this overflowing passion in my chest,

9
00:00:42.990 --> 00:00:45.070
I will go anywhere

10
00:00:45.070 --> 00:00:53.380
Seeking the light yet unseen

11
00:00:53.380 --> 00:00:58.940
When the summer sun stirs my heart's sails

12
00:01:03.400 --> 00:01:09.130
That's the signal to open the door to a new world

13
00:01:13.050 --> 00:01:18.060
Swaying on the waves, reaching beyond despair

14
00:01:18.060 --> 00:01:25.530
Aiming for the other side of the horizon

15
00:01:25.660 --> 00:01:31.330
I've just now begun to search, over the splashing waves

16
00:01:31.330 --> 00:01:34.510
For the everlasting world

17
00:01:35.950 --> 00:01:38.860
With this overflowing passion in my chest

18
00:01:38.860 --> 00:01:40.970
I will go anywhere

19
00:01:40.970 --> 00:01:47.560
Seeking the light yet unseen

20
00:01:49.980 --> 00:01:52.670
Is Conis gonna be alright?

21
00:01:52.670 --> 00:01:56.460
She wound up as an accomplice
because she tried to save us!

22
00:01:56.460 --> 00:01:59.130
She's gonna have hell to pay for sure!

23
00:01:59.130 --> 00:02:02.730
That old Sky Knight said
he'd look after her, but...

24
00:02:02.730 --> 00:02:06.100
Nah, he's weird,
but I don't think he's a bad guy.

25
00:02:06.100 --> 00:02:07.740
We don't have a choice.

26
00:02:07.740 --> 00:02:11.110
I wanna protect her,
but we can't take her with us, either.

27
00:02:11.600 --> 00:02:14.460
C'mon, this thing's so slow...

28
00:02:14.480 --> 00:02:17.880
Of course it is.
It's way heavier than a waver.

29
00:02:17.880 --> 00:02:19.070
Quit complaining!

30
00:02:19.120 --> 00:02:22.580
<b>Adventure on God's Island</b>

31
00:02:23.210 --> 00:02:26.570
Hey, look! What's with
that humongous forest?!

32
00:02:26.570 --> 00:02:28.140
Is that Upper Yard?!

33
00:02:28.140 --> 00:02:31.300
Amazing! Was there a forest
like this on the map?!

34
00:02:31.300 --> 00:02:37.180
Well, the map did show a forest,
but it was nothing like what's in front of us.

35
00:02:37.180 --> 00:02:38.260
This one's normal.

36
00:02:38.260 --> 00:02:42.170
People from 200 years ago
had that map, right?

37
00:02:42.170 --> 00:02:45.160
It might have been old even back then.

38
00:02:45.160 --> 00:02:48.990
It'd take at least 1,000 years
for trees to grow this massive!

39
00:02:49.550 --> 00:02:50.490
That's true...

40
00:02:50.490 --> 00:02:53.030
They sure are big trees!

41
00:02:54.490 --> 00:02:55.950
I wanna climb 'em!

42
00:03:00.880 --> 00:03:01.840
It's the entrance!

43
00:03:01.840 --> 00:03:04.120
Well, if we're gonna turn back,
now's our chance.

44
00:03:04.120 --> 00:03:05.790
You ready, Usopp?

45
00:03:05.790 --> 00:03:08.960
Huh? W-Well, I wouldn't
mind if we went back–

46
00:03:08.960 --> 00:03:09.760
Let's go!

47
00:03:09.760 --> 00:03:11.800
You weren't even gonna listen to me!

48
00:03:21.260 --> 00:03:23.970
I wanna go back...

49
00:03:36.500 --> 00:03:37.550
Something's here!

50
00:03:37.550 --> 00:03:39.040
Well, it is a forest!

51
00:03:39.040 --> 00:03:40.100
Yeah, it is.

52
00:03:40.100 --> 00:03:42.790
N-N-No, just hold on!
Look around you!

53
00:03:43.120 --> 00:03:44.890
It's nothing but shipwrecks!

54
00:03:44.890 --> 00:03:46.190
It is a forest!

55
00:03:46.190 --> 00:03:47.400
Yeah, it is.

56
00:03:47.400 --> 00:03:48.500
How are those related?!

57
00:03:48.880 --> 00:03:52.290
On top of that,
they're all sliced in half...

58
00:03:52.960 --> 00:03:53.840
Not again!

59
00:03:53.840 --> 00:03:56.130
Like I said, forests are
full of all sorts of–

60
00:03:56.130 --> 00:03:56.800
I was wrong!

61
00:03:57.240 --> 00:04:01.020
Hurry, full speed ahead!
Hurry! Paddle, paddle! Go!

62
00:04:01.020 --> 00:04:02.390
Huh? What's going on?

63
00:04:08.690 --> 00:04:10.120
A sickle monster!

64
00:04:10.120 --> 00:04:12.150
Watch out! There's another one!

65
00:04:14.620 --> 00:04:16.800
No... Not just one...!

66
00:04:19.570 --> 00:04:21.620
Paddle like hell!

67
00:04:30.460 --> 00:04:33.170
What's trying to kill us now?!

68
00:04:35.300 --> 00:04:37.280
Luffy, pay attention! Hit the brake!

69
00:04:37.280 --> 00:04:39.680
We're not gonna make it!
Take the wheel, Usopp!

70
00:04:39.680 --> 00:04:40.720
Gum-Gum...

71
00:04:40.720 --> 00:04:42.690
Luffy, what're you doing?!
Eyes forward!

72
00:04:42.690 --> 00:04:44.310
Just keep going straight!

73
00:04:44.310 --> 00:04:46.940
...Bazooka!

74
00:04:48.110 --> 00:04:49.050
Dodged it!

75
00:04:49.050 --> 00:04:50.310
That was close!

76
00:04:57.140 --> 00:04:58.860
We managed to evade it...

77
00:04:59.980 --> 00:05:03.220
but it's not looking good!
We can't go back now!

78
00:05:03.220 --> 00:05:05.440
We've come a long way
from the entrance!

79
00:05:05.440 --> 00:05:06.380
Wanna get off here?

80
00:05:06.380 --> 00:05:07.910
Don't be stupid! I'd die!

81
00:05:07.910 --> 00:05:09.370
Yeah, probably.

82
00:05:15.920 --> 00:05:17.920
What was that, a snake?!

83
00:05:18.260 --> 00:05:21.370
A lamprey. So,
a sky lamprey, I guess?

84
00:05:21.370 --> 00:05:24.430
One that big will do more
than suck a little blood!

85
00:05:25.350 --> 00:05:27.140
What a neat forest!

86
00:05:27.140 --> 00:05:31.320
Neat, my butt! If this is our ordeal,
I've already had enough!

87
00:05:31.320 --> 00:05:33.440
But we've only just entered the forest.

88
00:05:33.750 --> 00:05:39.240
We'll really be screwed if we stall
or stop on this milky road...

89
00:05:39.240 --> 00:05:41.650
Looks like our only choice
is to keep moving!

90
00:05:49.720 --> 00:05:50.960
There he is!

91
00:05:50.960 --> 00:05:51.790
Zoro!

92
00:05:51.790 --> 00:05:54.210
He's gonna lose to the sky shark!

93
00:06:02.880 --> 00:06:04.970
He went under again...

94
00:06:06.030 --> 00:06:08.330
Zoro isn't coming back up!

95
00:06:08.490 --> 00:06:11.390
Do you think... he got eaten?!

96
00:06:12.440 --> 00:06:14.610
Zoro was eaten!

97
00:06:14.610 --> 00:06:17.210
If he were eaten,
the clouds would turn red.

98
00:06:17.210 --> 00:06:20.140
Don't say such ominous things
with a straight face, Robin!

99
00:06:21.240 --> 00:06:24.530
You're finished!

100
00:06:40.910 --> 00:06:42.550
This is bad...

101
00:06:42.550 --> 00:06:46.050
Looks like swimming away
is out of the question.

102
00:06:46.050 --> 00:06:49.360
Why'd you punch it?!
I thought you were a swordsman.

103
00:06:49.360 --> 00:06:50.890
Zoro's so strong!

104
00:06:51.400 --> 00:06:55.770
I'm certain that this is
the interior of Upper Yard.

105
00:06:56.690 --> 00:07:00.320
It's almost as if this
is a sacrificial altar...

106
00:07:01.200 --> 00:07:03.530
Now there's a giant!

107
00:07:05.740 --> 00:07:07.850
No. That's a statue!

108
00:07:07.850 --> 00:07:11.200
Hey, but... it's totally a dead end.

109
00:07:11.200 --> 00:07:13.200
No, there are four entrances!

110
00:07:15.210 --> 00:07:19.540
And let me guess;
each one leads to a different place.

111
00:07:20.190 --> 00:07:21.570
"Ordeal of Swamp."

112
00:07:22.140 --> 00:07:23.910
"Ordeal of Iron."

113
00:07:23.910 --> 00:07:25.820
"Ordeal of String."

114
00:07:25.820 --> 00:07:27.260
"Ordeal of Balls."

115
00:07:28.060 --> 00:07:30.180
Can we go in any one of them?!

116
00:07:30.180 --> 00:07:34.060
Is "God" trying to play games
with us or something?

117
00:07:38.120 --> 00:07:43.360
Four ordeals...
Which one do we choose?

118
00:07:45.150 --> 00:07:49.240
A second-degree crime, huh?
Does God mean nothing to them?!

119
00:07:51.050 --> 00:07:54.700
Go ahead... Choose. We'll gladly
indulge you in any of them.

120
00:07:56.600 --> 00:07:59.210
It's a sin to live in ignorance.

121
00:08:01.150 --> 00:08:04.960
The means to attaining peace
do not lead one to heaven.

122
00:08:06.240 --> 00:08:07.470
Swamp!

123
00:08:08.350 --> 00:08:09.310
Iron!

124
00:08:10.570 --> 00:08:11.550
String!

125
00:08:13.310 --> 00:08:14.850
Balls!

126
00:08:17.340 --> 00:08:20.110
Choose an ordeal!

127
00:08:21.480 --> 00:08:22.860
So what do we choose?

128
00:08:22.860 --> 00:08:24.820
Alright! Let's go with "Balls"!

129
00:08:24.820 --> 00:08:26.590
Why's that, Luffy?

130
00:08:26.590 --> 00:08:28.440
Because balls are fun!

131
00:08:28.440 --> 00:08:29.950
That's your reason?!

132
00:08:29.950 --> 00:08:32.770
These are ordeals!
They're not gonna be fun!

133
00:08:32.770 --> 00:08:35.770
But I do agree with "Balls."

134
00:08:35.770 --> 00:08:39.920
It's the ordeal that
sounds the least violent.

135
00:08:39.920 --> 00:08:42.840
Then it's decided.
But don't let your guard down.

136
00:08:42.840 --> 00:08:45.870
We're on God's Island,
10,000 meters in the sky!

137
00:08:45.870 --> 00:08:48.190
Anything could happen here!

138
00:08:48.190 --> 00:08:50.530
Let's go! Balls!

139
00:09:00.480 --> 00:09:03.810
Hey, helmsman! Might wanna
keep your eyes open!

140
00:09:06.640 --> 00:09:08.620
Open or closed, it's still pitch black!

141
00:09:09.130 --> 00:09:11.010
Hey, is there other stuff like this?

142
00:09:11.010 --> 00:09:12.160
Like what?

143
00:09:12.160 --> 00:09:13.720
So with only four entrances...

144
00:09:13.720 --> 00:09:16.520
what if only one of them
was the lucky one?!

145
00:09:16.520 --> 00:09:19.560
Huh?! Don't say
that kind of crap now!

146
00:09:19.560 --> 00:09:21.830
What happens if we chose
the wrong one?!

147
00:09:21.830 --> 00:09:26.100
If it's the wrong one? Hmm...

148
00:09:26.100 --> 00:09:28.090
Maybe we'll fall off the sky island?

149
00:09:28.090 --> 00:09:30.700
We can't afford to fall off!

150
00:09:30.700 --> 00:09:33.050
It's 10,000 meters
to the Blue Sea, you know!

151
00:09:33.360 --> 00:09:36.270
This high up, 1,000 lives
would flash before your eyes!

152
00:09:36.270 --> 00:09:38.640
It's too crazy to even think about!

153
00:09:38.640 --> 00:09:42.290
Quit being dumbasses!
That's obviously not gonna hap–

154
00:10:01.830 --> 00:10:07.410
No way! You have
got to be kidding me!

155
00:10:23.230 --> 00:10:27.060
It wasn't just one! There's a whole
swarm of sky sharks!

156
00:10:27.060 --> 00:10:30.500
We'd be here until nightfall
if we fought every one of them.

157
00:10:30.500 --> 00:10:32.600
We'd never reach shore at that rate...

158
00:10:32.600 --> 00:10:36.300
But we can't just sit here, either.

159
00:10:38.520 --> 00:10:42.860
That giant lobster brought us
to one hell of a place...

160
00:10:42.860 --> 00:10:46.540
Do you suppose starving us here
is "Divine Reckoning"?

161
00:10:46.540 --> 00:10:50.000
Would a god really do
something so tasteless?

162
00:10:50.000 --> 00:10:52.780
Hard to say. I've never met one.

163
00:10:53.630 --> 00:10:55.900
This is bad...

164
00:10:55.900 --> 00:10:59.310
We can't set the boat in the water
with the hull like this.

165
00:11:00.010 --> 00:11:02.380
Try to fix the ship somehow, Chopper.

166
00:11:02.380 --> 00:11:04.640
Huh? Me?! Okay...

167
00:11:04.640 --> 00:11:07.560
Fix it? What are you up to?

168
00:11:07.560 --> 00:11:09.260
I've gotta get into this forest.

169
00:11:09.980 --> 00:11:12.840
For now, let's make this
our base of operations.

170
00:11:12.840 --> 00:11:16.300
I'm sure Luffy and the others
are headed here to search for us.

171
00:11:17.280 --> 00:11:20.800
It's like they say,
"If you get lost, stay put."

172
00:11:20.800 --> 00:11:22.750
You need to stay put the most!

173
00:11:33.170 --> 00:11:39.550
Say, Zoro... you said you're going
into the forest, but what for?

174
00:11:39.970 --> 00:11:42.940
There's a god on this island, right?
I'm gonna go meet him.

175
00:11:42.940 --> 00:11:48.020
I'm telling you, that's a bad idea!
What if you run into those freaks?!

176
00:11:48.490 --> 00:11:51.940
Good question. I guess
it all depends on how they act.

177
00:11:51.940 --> 00:11:54.990
Zoro... it's like you're
mightier than a god...

178
00:11:54.990 --> 00:11:57.560
He has priests on this
island too, you know!

179
00:11:57.560 --> 00:12:02.120
We can't make a god angry!
It's common sense, you know!

180
00:12:04.950 --> 00:12:06.660
Sorry, but...

181
00:12:07.960 --> 00:12:10.330
I've never once prayed to a god.

182
00:12:12.030 --> 00:12:14.300
So cool!

183
00:12:14.300 --> 00:12:18.370
I don't believe in them either,
so I don't owe this god a thing.

184
00:12:19.180 --> 00:12:21.000
Oh, mighty God!

185
00:12:21.000 --> 00:12:26.180
I have nothing to do with him!
Please don't punish me!

186
00:12:29.440 --> 00:12:31.850
That vine looks usable.

187
00:12:31.850 --> 00:12:33.980
You're right, good idea.

188
00:12:33.980 --> 00:12:36.960
Mind if I join you, Mr. Swordsman?

189
00:12:36.960 --> 00:12:39.980
Huh? Sure, but don't go
slowing me down!

190
00:12:39.980 --> 00:12:41.000
Hold on!

191
00:12:41.000 --> 00:12:43.060
Where are you going, Robin?!

192
00:12:43.060 --> 00:12:44.290
Look at this.

193
00:12:45.440 --> 00:12:49.530
This altar was built 
at least 1,000 years ago.

194
00:12:49.530 --> 00:12:51.330
– At least... 1,000 years?!
– At least... 1,000 years?!

195
00:12:51.810 --> 00:12:56.920
Historical findings like this
make me prickle with excitement!

196
00:12:58.760 --> 00:13:03.730
Where there is a rich history,
there will be an abundance of relics.

197
00:13:05.520 --> 00:13:09.770
Perhaps even a few jewels
that would help pay for ship repairs.

198
00:13:11.200 --> 00:13:12.540
I'm coming too!

199
00:13:12.540 --> 00:13:14.940
Really?! Even after you
were so scared?!

200
00:13:16.520 --> 00:13:18.200
It's for investigating history!

201
00:13:18.200 --> 00:13:19.870
Those are belly signs...

202
00:13:32.920 --> 00:13:36.300
Do you have to make that sound?

203
00:13:45.640 --> 00:13:47.530
Robin is amazing!

204
00:13:48.250 --> 00:13:49.970
She did it so easily...

205
00:13:54.030 --> 00:13:56.020
This might be a bit too high up...

206
00:13:56.020 --> 00:13:59.300
It's about fifty meters!
If you slip, you'll die!

207
00:13:59.300 --> 00:14:01.870
Stop saying morbid things!

208
00:14:07.310 --> 00:14:09.870
I really am a goner if I fall!

209
00:14:10.320 --> 00:14:11.410
Nami...

210
00:14:18.820 --> 00:14:21.220
T-Too fast! I can't stop!

211
00:14:24.800 --> 00:14:26.180
See? You have courage.

212
00:14:28.540 --> 00:14:30.890
I apologize for the inconvenience.

213
00:14:30.890 --> 00:14:31.740
Not at all.

214
00:14:31.740 --> 00:14:35.290
That's because you didn't go,
"Aah-eeh-ah-eeh-aaaaaah!"

215
00:14:35.290 --> 00:14:36.860
Is that the issue here?!

216
00:14:39.690 --> 00:14:42.110
This certainly is a big forest...

217
00:14:44.240 --> 00:14:46.760
Okay, Chopper!
You're in charge of the ship!

218
00:14:46.760 --> 00:14:47.740
You've got this!

219
00:14:47.740 --> 00:14:49.180
We'll be back soon!

220
00:14:49.180 --> 00:14:54.160
Right! Be careful, everyone!
Come back safe!

221
00:14:57.390 --> 00:15:00.460
I guess Nami will be okay
since she has Zoro and Robin.

222
00:15:01.230 --> 00:15:03.760
I'm too scared to go...

223
00:15:04.250 --> 00:15:06.930
Everyone is so brave and amazing!

224
00:15:06.930 --> 00:15:10.480
I wonder if I'll
be brave someday, too...

225
00:15:10.480 --> 00:15:14.160
Anyway, I'll do everything I can now!

226
00:15:14.770 --> 00:15:17.770
Taking care of the ship by myself
in a dangerous forest

227
00:15:17.770 --> 00:15:20.270
is proof that everyone has faith in me!

228
00:15:20.270 --> 00:15:21.630
I gotta do my best!

229
00:15:22.510 --> 00:15:26.350
That's right! I'm all alone
in this dangerous place–

230
00:15:28.730 --> 00:15:32.450
I'm the one in the most danger!

231
00:15:35.290 --> 00:15:36.750
We're alive...

232
00:15:37.460 --> 00:15:41.410
I seriously thought we were
gonna fall 10,000 meters...

233
00:15:43.310 --> 00:15:46.920
You freaked Usopp out
with that nonsense, Luffy!

234
00:15:46.920 --> 00:15:49.340
That was scary!
I thought I was gonna die!

235
00:15:54.990 --> 00:15:57.310
But still, what is this place?

236
00:15:57.310 --> 00:15:59.770
They're balls. Definitely balls.

237
00:16:06.920 --> 00:16:09.690
They're little balls of island cloud...

238
00:16:10.590 --> 00:16:13.710
Awesome! They're like big snow!

239
00:16:13.710 --> 00:16:16.710
What a weird place! It's so neat!

240
00:16:19.040 --> 00:16:22.420
The milky road leads
above the trees...

241
00:16:22.420 --> 00:16:25.320
But what part of this is an ordeal?

242
00:16:25.320 --> 00:16:26.800
Who knows?

243
00:16:27.390 --> 00:16:31.240
It'd be great if there's nothing at all,
but I doubt that's the case.

244
00:16:31.240 --> 00:16:34.440
Maybe we did get the lucky entrance!

245
00:16:34.440 --> 00:16:38.570
I bet if we chose one of the others,
we'd be in trouble right about now!

246
00:16:39.370 --> 00:16:41.740
Y-Yeah! You might be right!

247
00:16:41.740 --> 00:16:42.620
Right?!

248
00:16:42.620 --> 00:16:44.560
You idiots, don't let your guard down!

249
00:16:44.560 --> 00:16:47.900
Would they really let
criminals off without a hitch?

250
00:16:47.900 --> 00:16:49.700
Think about it!

251
00:16:50.080 --> 00:16:53.780
There might be traps like earlier...

252
00:16:53.780 --> 00:16:54.950
Stay alert!

253
00:16:57.000 --> 00:16:59.000
Let's just keep moving...

254
00:16:59.000 --> 00:17:01.580
I'm thirsty! Let's have some tea!

255
00:17:01.580 --> 00:17:04.840
Huh? Yeah, let's!
Open the rice crackers in your bag!

256
00:17:04.840 --> 00:17:06.510
Oh, good idea!

257
00:17:06.510 --> 00:17:07.970
You sons of...

258
00:17:07.970 --> 00:17:10.110
C'mon, just one rice cracker!

259
00:17:10.110 --> 00:17:11.410
Yeah! Let's eat, let's eat!

260
00:17:11.410 --> 00:17:14.760
Knock it off! Listen,
I'm gonna keep steering.

261
00:17:14.760 --> 00:17:17.010
You guys keep watch on both sides!

262
00:17:22.410 --> 00:17:25.320
It took us really high up
at some point...

263
00:17:25.740 --> 00:17:28.060
But it's strange...

264
00:17:28.060 --> 00:17:34.620
There are four priests, so I assumed
each entrance would lead us to one...

265
00:17:35.640 --> 00:17:37.120
but I guess not.

266
00:17:37.120 --> 00:17:39.790
Hey, Usopp! Pass!

267
00:17:39.790 --> 00:17:43.040
Okay! I got it! Pass!

268
00:17:43.040 --> 00:17:44.670
I told you to keep watch!

269
00:17:49.170 --> 00:17:50.010
A snake!

270
00:17:50.800 --> 00:17:53.900
You jerk! Beat it!

271
00:17:59.130 --> 00:18:01.530
That was a surprise! Why would...?

272
00:18:02.460 --> 00:18:04.400
Sanji! Look out! There's another cloud!

273
00:18:04.400 --> 00:18:05.710
Kick it far away!

274
00:18:05.710 --> 00:18:09.860
Dammit! Are all these
floating things snake eggs?!

275
00:18:27.740 --> 00:18:29.090
– This isn't good...
– This isn't good...

276
00:18:30.510 --> 00:18:35.470
What's the deal with these balls?!

277
00:18:38.090 --> 00:18:41.420
There's no telling what's inside!

278
00:18:43.280 --> 00:18:46.520
These clouds are called
surprise clouds!

279
00:18:46.940 --> 00:18:48.480
Surprise clouds?!

280
00:18:50.010 --> 00:18:51.110
Heso!

281
00:18:51.110 --> 00:18:51.820
Who's there?!

282
00:18:54.670 --> 00:18:58.350
Thank you for choosing my Ordeal of Balls!

283
00:18:55.570 --> 00:19:00.490
<b>Satori of the Forest
Skypiea Priest</b>

284
00:19:01.160 --> 00:19:03.390
What's with the dumpling freak?

285
00:19:08.880 --> 00:19:11.800
Don't tell me he's a priest?!

286
00:19:15.050 --> 00:19:17.450
You're the ball in the Ordeal of Balls?!

287
00:19:17.450 --> 00:19:20.350
Quit dancing around!
Who the hell are you?!

288
00:19:24.000 --> 00:19:26.830
Wow, he seems dumber
than I expected...

289
00:19:26.830 --> 00:19:30.730
Didn't Nami and the old guy
say they were really strong?

290
00:19:33.640 --> 00:19:34.700
Hey! Dumpling!

291
00:19:35.040 --> 00:19:37.610
Nami's group had better be safe!

292
00:19:38.380 --> 00:19:39.700
You mean the sacrifices?

293
00:19:39.700 --> 00:19:43.450
If so, I wouldn't know!
But they'll die if they're left alone!

294
00:19:43.450 --> 00:19:46.400
And even if they escape,
they're still going to die!

295
00:19:47.460 --> 00:19:48.810
Say what?!

296
00:19:48.810 --> 00:19:51.180
You should worry about yourselves.

297
00:19:51.180 --> 00:19:56.430
In case you didn't realize it, you'll need
to defeat me to continue ahead!

298
00:19:59.390 --> 00:20:01.920
Okay, Luffy! Here he comes! Get 'im!

299
00:20:01.920 --> 00:20:03.930
Alright! I'll knock him out of the air!

300
00:20:04.270 --> 00:20:05.680
Gum-Gum...

301
00:20:06.090 --> 00:20:07.770
Oh, you're going to stretch?

302
00:20:10.400 --> 00:20:13.360
...Pistol!

303
00:20:28.210 --> 00:20:29.120
No way!

304
00:20:29.120 --> 00:20:30.000
Luffy!

305
00:20:41.320 --> 00:20:43.840
Luffy?! Hey! You're okay, right?!

306
00:20:43.840 --> 00:20:46.490
A regular hit shouldn't affect you!

307
00:20:46.490 --> 00:20:47.890
A regular hit?

308
00:20:48.670 --> 00:20:51.520
This is a bit different
from a regular hit!

309
00:20:51.990 --> 00:20:53.980
The hell do you mean by that?!

310
00:20:53.980 --> 00:20:55.860
An upward kick with the right leg...

311
00:20:55.860 --> 00:20:57.360
Collier– What?!

312
00:20:57.750 --> 00:21:02.810
Those with enough discipline and training
are given the power of mantra.

313
00:21:03.420 --> 00:21:07.040
Impossible! He predicted
my movements?!

314
00:21:18.200 --> 00:21:19.720
Sanji!

315
00:21:21.030 --> 00:21:23.180
It is different from a hit!

316
00:21:23.190 --> 00:21:23.920
Impact!

317
00:21:28.650 --> 00:21:31.600
The shock destroys
the body from the inside!

318
00:21:35.520 --> 00:21:38.640
D-Dammit! Sanji! Usopp!

319
00:21:42.360 --> 00:21:47.120
Yeah, I'm alright...
But what the hell was that?!

320
00:21:47.120 --> 00:21:50.460
No idea at all...! He's a mystery!

321
00:21:52.750 --> 00:21:55.360
My name is Satori!

322
00:21:55.360 --> 00:21:59.420
I am one of the priests
of the almighty God Enel!

323
00:21:59.420 --> 00:22:02.130
I own the vearth
in these Lost Woods.

324
00:22:02.620 --> 00:22:03.970
Lost Woods?

325
00:22:03.970 --> 00:22:04.930
Yes!

326
00:22:06.570 --> 00:22:08.800
That is what we call this forest!

327
00:22:09.430 --> 00:22:11.140
And...

328
00:22:13.930 --> 00:22:16.820
your boat will be lost within it!

329
00:22:17.680 --> 00:22:18.900
The boat is taking off!

330
00:22:19.390 --> 00:22:24.140
Your boat will now speed along
the milky road at random

331
00:22:24.140 --> 00:22:28.010
and eventually leave through
this forest's only exit!

332
00:22:28.010 --> 00:22:31.600
I'm sure you realize it,
but losing a dial boat

333
00:22:31.600 --> 00:22:35.580
is the same as losing your way
to the sacrificial altar.

334
00:22:36.970 --> 00:22:41.090
So you must find and board
the boat before that happens.

335
00:22:41.090 --> 00:22:46.300
Of course, these countless surprise
clouds and I will not allow that.

336
00:22:47.420 --> 00:22:52.020
Welcome to the sacred ground
of Upper Yard!

337
00:22:57.120 --> 00:23:02.400
This is the Lost Woods' Ordeal of Balls,
which has a 10 percent survival rate!

338
00:23:02.400 --> 00:23:06.110
A 10 percent survival rate?!
